title.value: Outcomes of guidelines from health technology assessment organizations in community-based primary care: a systematic mixed studies review.
title.justification: The title is specified at the top and also in the citation of the article.
title.quote:
Outcomes of
guidelines from health technology assessment organizations in community-based
primary care: a systematic mixed studies review.

extractions.description: The paper conducts a systematic mixed studies review focusing on the outcomes of guidelines produced by health technology assessment organizations in community-based primary care. It analyzes various outcomes such as user satisfaction, information use, and impacts on health services and patient health.

type.justification: The paper involves the collection and analysis of data from empirical studies, focusing on outcomes of guidelines in community-based primary care.
type.quote: We performed a systematic mixed studies review of empirical studies...

name.value: Health Technology Assessment in Primary Care
name.justification: The research focuses on the outcomes of guidelines from health technology assessment organizations in primary care settings.
name.quote:
Health technology assessment (HTA) organizations generate guidelines to inform
healthcare practices toward improved health outcomes.

name.justification: The paper discusses guidelines produced by HTA organizations, which include clinical practice guidelines.
name.quote:
In this study, we did not focus on guidelines that guide how to conduct HTA but rather on
guidelines produced by organizations that conduct HTA.
